<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="61" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,338]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,321,151,177]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">Remarks:</emphasis>
Examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[561,611,152,178]" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
specimen revealed that the species is pale yellow with a black spot on the vertex, the median carina on the head is not raised, the male pygophore has long, slender ventral processes exceeding the pygophore and the aedeagal shaft has a large, elongate, basal hood-like process. These characters showed that the species does not belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1903" box="[817,932,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[817,932,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">Pythamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but to 
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1912" box="[1026,1256,272,298]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Onukia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1026,1112,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="61">Onukia</emphasis>
Matsumura
</taxonomicName>
and hence the generic transfer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
